Instead of putting something in other servers logs (which may never be
looked at) or sending mail to postmaster, isn't the correct thing to do
send mail to the maintainer of the offending zone(s) which is supposed
to be in the SOA records?  In all the cases you describe, there should
be at least one SOA record (e.g., the one for EDU even if you can't get
the one for MIT.EDU).  I agree that more attention to problem
debugability would be a good thing.

